 in SLA contexts. The editors have brought together a diverse range of theoretical perspectives on the self to allow the reader to appreciate the insights that each approach contributes to overall understandings of the self in the domain of second language acquisition and foreign language learning.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Apr 2022) 0aLanguage acquisitionxPsychological aspects. 0aLanguage acquisitionxResearchxMethodology. 0aLanguage acquisitionxStudy and teaching. 0aLanguage and languagesxStudy and teachingxPsychological aspects. 0aPsycholinguistics. 7aLANGUAGE ARTS & DISCIPLINES / Linguistics / Psycholinguistics.2bisacsh  aL2 Self.  aL2 identity.  aSLA.  aSecond Language Acquisition.  aSelf-Concept.  aSelf-efficacy in SLA.  aThe Self.  aforeign language learning.  aidentity.  athe self in SLA .1 aClément, Richard, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHemmi, Chantal, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aIrie, Kay, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMercer, Sarah, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMercer, Sarah, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aMills, Nicole, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aNorthoff, Georg, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aNorton, Bonny, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aRubio, Fernando D., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aRyan, Stephen, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSampasivam, Sinthujaa, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aTaylor, Florentina, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 